  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6609.4 sitting just above the GEX flip at 6607, dealers are in positive gamma territory and will be selling delta into any push toward the massive 6610-6620 wall cluster (nearly 105B in combined GEX). The recent GEX surge of 44-62% in the last 1-5 minutes indicates heavy options flow that's creating significant dealer hedging obligations around current levels. Key resistance lies at 6620 (max positive gamma) where dealers will aggressively sell rallies, while 6590 represents the primary support where negative gamma forces dealers to buy dips.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get pinned between 6590-6620 with selling pressure on any move toward 6615-6620.",
